owl:Ontology.dc:description: An ontology that describes the Generic Feature Format Version 3 (GFF3) by Lincoln Stein (http://www.sequenceontology.org/resources/gff3.html). The ontology was inspired by previous work of Robert Hoehndorf's RDF2OWL (http://code.google.com/p/rdf2owl).
owl:Ontology.dc:title: Generic Feature Format Version 3 Ontology (GFF3O)
owl:Ontology.dc:creator: Joachim Baran

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: attributes
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Tag name/value pair attributes of a feature that are not covered by object-/data-properties of the ontology. Tags that are represented as object-/data-properties are: ID, Name, Alias, Parent, Target, Gap, Derives_from, Dbxref, Ontology_term, Ontology_term, or Is_circular

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: parent
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link out to the parent feature.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: contains
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Relationship that describes which features belong to a feature set.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: region
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: FALDO "Region" instance replacement for a feature's start, stop, strand properties.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: species
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: NCBI Taxonomy Ontology "NCBITaxon_1" (or sub-classes) instance that denotes the species for a feature set.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: set_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Set class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: feature_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Feature class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: dbxref
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A database cross-reference to associate a sequence alteration to its representation in another database.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: ontology_term
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A cross-reference to an ontology term that is associated with a feature.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: target
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Identifies the target that the features aligns to.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: target_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Target class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: strand
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Strand of a target -- if applicable.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: derives_from
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes a temporal relationship between two features, where the object denotes the subjects origin.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: region
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: FALDO "Region" instance replacement for a target's start, stop, strand properties.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: seqid
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: ID of the landmark that establishes the coordinate system for the current feature.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: source
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A free text qualifier that describes the algorithm or operating procedure that generated this feature. For example, the name of the software that generated this feature or a database name.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: type
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Type of the feature, which is either a term from the "lite" version of the Sequence Ontology (SOFA), a term from the full Sequence Ontology (SO) that is a child of sequence_feature (SO:0000110), or a SOFA or SO accession number.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: start
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Start coordinate of the feature on the seqid landmark.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: end
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: End coordinate of the feature on the seqid landmark.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: score
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Score of the feature. For example, an E-value for sequence similarity features or a P-value for ab initio gene prediction features.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: phase
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Phase for "CDS" features. It indicates where the feature begins with reference to the reading frame. For forward strand features, phase is counted from the start field, whilst for reverse strand features, phase is counted from the end field.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: tag
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Tag name of a feature attribute.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: version
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Version of the GFF3 specification that defines the feature set contents.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: build
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Name of a genome assembly build that denotes the provenance of features in a feature set. For example, 'NCBI 36' or 'FlyBase r4.1'.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: set_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Set class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: feature_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Feature class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: attribute_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Attribute class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: dbxref_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with DBXRef class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: name
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Name of an external database. For example, "dbSNP" or "OMIM".

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: xref
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: External database identifier. For example, for dbSNP, this identifier could be "rs3131969".

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: name
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Name of a feature, which can be used for display purposes. The name is not a unique property among features.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: alias
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An alternative name for a feature. This can be another descriptive name of a feature, such as a locus name or accession number.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: target_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Target class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: target_id
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: ID or accession of the target alignment.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: start
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Start coordinate of the target.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: end
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: End coordinate of the target.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: gap
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Gap describing the feature/target alignment if the sequences are not collinear. The formal description of this property has been lost due to a dead link in the GFF3 specification.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: note
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A free text note.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: is_circular
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes whether a feature is circular or not.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Set
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Set of genomic sequence features, whose identifiers are unique within the set.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Attribute
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describes additional feature attributes besides ID, Name, Alias, Parent, Target, Gap, Derives_from, Dbxref, Ontology_term, Ontology_term, or Is_circular.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Strand
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class describing a genomic strand. Instances of the class (individuals) are used to denote forward-/reverse-strands, etc.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Target
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates a feature's "target" of a nucleotide-to-nucleotide or protein-to-nucleotide alignment.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: UnknownStrand
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Strand was not determined, which leaves it open whether the location is on the positive (forward) or negative (reverse) strand.
